The paper deals with optimization problems related to graphs, specifically the nonuniform sparsest cut problem. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses spectral methods and semidefinite programming, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of the sparsity measure used in the problem.
